# Red Hat UI Icons

## Rule
- **Never import icons from `@patternfly/react-icons` in widget or dashboard UI code.**
- **Always import from `@app/icons/rhUiIcons`** — use the exported RH UI icons or their PatternFly-name aliases (e.g. `CheckCircleIcon`, `GripVerticalIcon`).
- **`src/app/icons/rhUiIcons.ts` is the only file** that may import from `@patternfly/react-icons` for RH UI outline icons.

## When adding a new icon
1. Check whether an RH UI equivalent exists in `@patternfly/react-icons` (`RhUi*Icon`).
2. Export it from `rhUiIcons.ts` — prefer a descriptive alias if replacing a common PatternFly name.
3. Use the alias in components so call sites stay readable.

## Widget surfaces covered
- Dashboard widget grid and cards (`homepageWidgetGrid.tsx`, product widget modules)
- Widget bank, add-widgets drawer, help panel
- Dashboard Hub editor and related modals
